5:
Mmm, what's that smell? Is that
cinnamon?
9: Oh, I'm sorry, I didn't notice you there.
18:
No, not really. I just thought that I
could replicate Shibuyan medicine
with these ingredients.
22:
Shibuya's medicines are really
something else! They're all super
effective and taste much better
than you'd expect!
26: Hartlief, are you getting enough rest?
29:
You've been working for three days
straight now.
33:
Y-yes, I'm fine. I'm getting proper
nutrition and everything.
38:
From that energy drink of yours, you
mean? You consider that nutritious?
43:
Aheh... Yes, I adjusted the recipe so it
shouldn't have any adverse effects.
48: Hartlief, it's time to take a break.
52:
Why not take the rest of the day off?
You don't want to fall ill yourself, do
you?
61:
But wait! Don't you think there are
tons of people who need rest more
than I do? That gives me an idea!
66:
What's that I smell? Aroma oil? And
was that Harlisha?
72:
Welcome to the top secret
Self-Indulgent Shindig!
80:
It's a place for those that work
nonstop to take a breather and
relax.
83:
You must be here because you're a
workaholic.
87: I don't know, I wouldn't say that.
91:
C'mon, you're not fooling anyone.
This place seems perfect for you.
94:
But me? I have my own ways to
indulge myself, so I'm just gonna
head out and hit the town.
99:
Oh no, Nimbus, you're giving your
liver a rest today.
102:
You've been drinking more these
days, right? You need rest too. That's
an order from a medical
professional.
107:
Oh, no. No, no, no, no, no.
It's the holiday festival, I can't NOT—
112:
Nimbus. Self indulgence sometimes
means indulging in what your body
needs.
116:
That's not what that word means at
all...
121:
Look, they have a point. They're just
looking out for us, so let's take it
easy today!
132:
Harlisha and I made this scent.
What do you think?
136:
Hmm... Wow. I can feel my muscles
relaxing already. I could get used to
this.
140:
I've been meaning to thank you
again, Alk.
143:
I wouldn't have a garden—nor my
research—had you not brought me
to this village.
146:
And most recently my research has
led me to studying Shibuyan
medicine. Admittedly, the energy
drink was a bit of a failure.
151:
I'm happy to hear you're doing well.
But I think you'd be doing just as well
even without us.
155:
Yawn... I also have goals... And even
though it might be selfish, I decided
them for myself, so I work hard...
162:
But I think that's exactly why we
should all take a break today.
166:
A day of relaxing before we go back
to our duties full-force tomorrow.
That's what I'm gonna do.
170: Yeah... Yawn... Sounds like a plan...
175:
The two of them are sleeping like
babies.
179: Yes. Your plan was a great success.
183:
But you spent more time caring for
our guests. Hehe, you're hopeless
after all.
187:
I came to Palpebra because I want
to help as many people as possible.
190:
But I still have a lot to learn. I haven't
even found that legendary herb...
195:
When I feel worn out or that I have
failed, I practice self-affirmations.
199: You should give it a try, Hartlief.
206:
You're doing great, Hartlief! You're
trying super hard, just like everyone
else!
211:
That's the spirit! I'm glad to see
you've both upped your
self-indulgence game!
215:
What do you say we kick it up
another notch?
219: Good work, Hartlief. Keep it up, girl.
222:
After all, there are plenty of patients
waiting for your healing touch
tomorrow!
